OL,3,CWoman dies after being attacked by two
OL,4,Cdogs in Wolverhampton
OL,6,FWest Midlands Police said due to the
OL,7,Fcontinued aggression of both dogs when
OL,8,Femergency services arrived, they were
OL,9,Fhumanely destroyed.
OL,11,FA 37-year-old man was arrested on
OL,12,Fsuspicion of being in charge of a dog
OL,13,Fdangerously out of control and causing
OL,14,Finjury resulting in death.
OL,16,FHe was taken to hospital after also
OL,17,Freceiving injuries to his hand.
OL,19,FFurther enquiries are being carried
OL,20,Fout into the two dogs who are not
OL,21,Fbelieved to be a banned breed.
